# Command glimpse

## What does this command do:

A CLI that extracts structured context from your git history — for AI agents, PR descriptions, and standups.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: pip install --user gitglimpse
For Raspberry Pi install using: pip install --user gitglimpse
For Mac install using: pip install --user gitglimpse

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/glimpse
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/glimpse
For Mac run: ~/.local/bin/glimpse

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/dino-zecevic/gitglimpse

## Command options

# Generate a standup update from recent commits (auto-detects since last standup)
glimpse standup

# Standup for commits since a specific period
glimpse standup --since "2 days ago"

# Standup across multiple repos (comma-separated paths)
glimpse standup --repos "api,frontend,landing"

# Output standup as JSON
glimpse standup --json

# Save standup output to a markdown file
glimpse standup --format markdown -o daily.md

# Filter by author email
glimpse standup --author you@example.com

# Skip LLM, use offline template formatter
glimpse standup --no-llm

# Use a local Ollama LLM
glimpse standup --local-llm

# Use a specific Ollama model
glimpse standup --local-llm --model qwen2.5-coder:latest

# Generate a weekly summary (last 7 days by default)
glimpse week

# Weekly summary for a custom date range
glimpse week --since "14 days ago" --until "7 days ago"

# Weekly summary as JSON
glimpse week --json

# Generate a PR summary (compares current branch to main)
glimpse pr

# PR summary against a different base branch
glimpse pr --base develop

# PR summary using diff context for LLM
glimpse pr --context diffs

# PR summary as JSON
glimpse pr --json

# Initialize Claude Code slash-command files in current repo
glimpse init

# Initialize both Claude Code and Cursor slash-command files
glimpse init --claude --cursor

# Overwrite existing slash-command files
glimpse init --force

# Show current gitglimpse configuration
glimpse config show

# Interactive LLM setup (choose mode, configure API keys)
glimpse config setup

# Install shell completion for the current shell
glimpse --install-completion
